               <head>Imdad fi ma'asir al-ajdad</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Imdād fī maʾās̲ir al-ajdād by Valī Allāh Dihlavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91002492 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85112612 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008108146" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3985-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_71535292">Valī Allāh Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_71535292" type="supplied">ولى الله دهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21933">Imdād fī maʾās̲ir al-ajdād</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21933">امداد فى مآثر الاجداد</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Short hagiographic account treated as a separate work describing the author's ancestors</p>
                        <p>The work forms the whole of <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">faṣl</term> 1 of <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">qism</term> 3 from the larger work on the miracles and contributions of the author's family and teachers, the <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Anfās al-ʿārifīn</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Each qism and every faṣl has been treated as a detachable work</p>
                        <p>According to Storey, the Hijrī year specified in the colophon (<date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1213</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1799</date>) may be a mistake, and should read <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1312</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian">1895</date>, in keeping with the period of transcription
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
